in.iask.electonrush.commands

Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • in.iask.electonrush.commands.Command
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CommandGroup, TimedCommand

    public abstract class Command
extends java.lang.Object
    The command class defines a command that can be submitted to the scheduler for execution. Commands may require one or more Subsystem. When a command is started, all commands that requires one or more subsystems that this command requires will be canceled. A Time out may be provided to the constructor or set by calling the setTimeout method. This timeout has NO effect on the execution of the command, it only effects the isTimedOut method.
    Author:
    ElectricFish
